# Part 2 – User and Group Creation

Date: 26/02/2026

## Objective
Create local users automatically from a CSV file and assign them to the correct groups.

---

## Local Groups

The following local groups were verified/created:

- Innkaup
- Sala
- Yfirstjorn
- Allir

![Groups created](../imagenes/parte2_grupos.png)

---

## CSV File

A file named `usuarios.csv` was created with the following structure:

- Nombre (Username)
- Password
- Grupo (Group)
- FullName

The file contains 9 employees.

![CSV Content](../imagenes/parte2_csv.png)

---

## PowerShell Script

A script named `crear_usuarios.ps1` was created to:

- Import user data from the CSV file
- Create local users
- Assign passwords
- Add users to their corresponding group
- Add all users to the group "Allir"

The script executed successfully without errors.

![Script execution](../imagenes/parte2_script.png)

---

## Verification

It was verified that:

- All 9 users were created
- All users are enabled
- Each user belongs to their corresponding group
- All users belong to the "Allir" group

![Group verification](../imagenes/parte2_verificacion_grupos.png)


# Part 3 – Folder Structure and Permissions

Date: 26/02/2026

## Objective
Create a folder structure for each department and configure proper NTFS permissions.

---

## Folder Structure

The following structure was created:

C:\Gogn

- Innkaup
- Sala
- Yfirstjorn
- Sameign

![Folder structure](../imagenes/parte3_estructura.png)

---

## Permission Configuration

Inheritance was removed using:

icacls /inheritance:r

Then specific permissions were assigned:

- Administrators → Full Control
- User monti → Full Control
- Corresponding group → Modify
- Sameign → Group Allir with Modify permission

Permissions were verified using the icacls command.

![Permissions configured](../imagenes/parte3_permisos.png)

---

## Test Files

A .txt file was created inside each folder to verify correct functionality:

- Innkaup.txt
- Sala.txt
- Yfirstjorn.txt
- Sameign.txt

![Test files](../imagenes/parte3_archivos.png)


# Part 4 – Security Configuration

Date: 26/02/2026

## Password Policy

The system password policy was configured with the following settings:

- Minimum password length: 8 characters
- Maximum password age: 90 days
- Password history: 5 passwords remembered
- Account lockout policy configured

Verification was performed using:

net accounts

![Password policy](../imagenes/parte4_politica_contrasenas.png)

---

## Firewall Configuration

Windows Defender Firewall was configured with the following rules:

1. Block all inbound traffic
2. Allow ICMPv4 (Ping) only

Rules created:

- "Bloquear todo entrante" → Action: Block
- "Permitir Ping" → Action: Allow

The rules are enabled and applied to all profiles.

![Firewall rules](../imagenes/parte4_firewall.png)

---

## Final Result

The system meets the required security standards:

- Users properly organized
- NTFS permissions correctly configured
- Password policy enforced
- Firewall restricting inbound traffic
